fieldTemplates.label: Exhibit Uploaded to Files Section? (Appropriate Exhibit Signed?)

events.name: No Route Changes, Make Ready Accepted
Submit Prelim Make Ready to Licensee
Notify Licensee of Actual Make Ready

actions.name: Email Lic. to Sign and Upload Exhibit

parameters.body: The appropriate exhibit has not been signed and uploaded to the files section of this project.  Please do so and advance the project to Exhibit Signed and Uploaded.
parameters.subject: Sign and Upload Exhibit

actions.name: Email Assignee: Add scheduled week in Remarks section

parameters.body: When this project has been added to the schedule, include the schedule details in the Remarks section of this project.
parameters.subject: Holding for Scheduling

parameters.body: Please sign and upload the appropriate exhibit to the files section of this project.
parameters.subject: Sign and Upload Exhibit

parameters.body: No make ready is required for this project. Please advance the project status to Accepted or Cancel Project.
parameters.subject: No Make Ready Required

parameters.body: The addition of this project would cause your companys pole count within the 45-Day process to exceed 300.  Please resubmit this project when the amount of poles in the 45-Day process is such that the addition of this project would not cause the total number of poles to exceed 300.
parameters.subject: 300 Poles Exceeded

parameters.body: Following our post construction inspection, the installation requires corrections. Please contact the PNM Joint Use department for more details.
parameters.subject: Corrections Required

parameters.body: This project has been sent to scheduling.
parameters.subject: Project Added to Schedule

parameters.body: To remove poles from this project, load the project in map view, set the project as "active," and select Remove Stations from the Action dropdown. Select the stations to be removed, and click Selected Stations.
parameters.subject: Removing Poles

actions.name: Email Licensee: Remove can't add Poles

parameters.body: According to PNM policy, poles can be removed from a project at this point, but not added.  To remove poles, advance the project to the status Remove Poles from Project.
parameters.subject: Re-Evaluating Route

parameters.body: Some or all of the pole forms need completed before this project can be submitted to PNM.
parameters.subject: Pole Forms Incomplete

parameters.body: Construction for this project can begin.  When attached, advance project to Construction Complete, or this project will be considered void.
parameters.subject: Begin Construction

parameters.body: Please verify that the licensee has signed and uploaded the appropriate exhibit to the files section of this project.  If not, advance the project to Exhibit Not Signed and Uploaded
parameters.subject: Verify Signed Exhibit Uploaded

parameters.body: The loaded cost report has been sent to joint use admin and is ready for review.
parameters.subject: Ready for Review

parameters.body: This project is ready for you to prepare backup documentation for billing.
parameters.subject: Prepare Documentation

parameters.body: PNM Construction is complete for this project, proceed to attach.
parameters.subject: Proceed to Attach

actions.name: 14 Days, Notify Lic of Actual MR

parameters.body: Corrections to this project are required before it can be accepted. Please see Remarks in the project info section for more details.
parameters.subject: Corrections Required

actions.name: Z14 Day Clock for Lic to Accept Actual Make Ready

parameters.body: This project has been canceled by the Licensee.  See project logs for more details.
parameters.subject: Canceled Project

parameters.body: Before advancing this project's status, generate the project's SPIDACalc file. To do this, load the project into Map View, set the project as Active, and select Create Calc File in the Action dropdown.  Next, select each pole in the project in the correct order and click Save File. When the file successfully saves, advance the project to the next status.
parameters.subject: Generate Project SPIDACalc File
